<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1488" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1488">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/105.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your July 31. Cable statement of exactly all you have done to prevent
                            violence to the person of ex-President Leguía and his son. The
                            Department desires that you leave undone nothing you can properly do to
                            save the lives of these gentlemen and of the Vice President. Interview
                            the President before reporting.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>